        '**ISO 23247 – Digital Twin Framework for Manufacturing** (2021): Defines a development framework for DTs in manufacturing, organized into four parts. Part 2 (Reference Architecture) is most relevant, introducing entity-based design (e.g., Observable Manufacturing Elements, Digital Twin Entities, User Entities).'
      ],
      'specifications_followed': [
        '**Entity-Based Reference Architecture (RA)**: Modular design where each entity (e.g., OME, DTE, User Entity) implements specific DT functionalities.',
